# quack-auth project conventions

**Source of truth** for coding and layout conventions in this repo.

When the Developer states a **new convention** (or you extend an existing section here):

1. Update **this file** with the full convention text.
2. Add a **one-line pointer** in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) only ŌĆö do not duplicate detail there.
3. **Update related Docusaurus docs in the same branch/PR** ŌĆö **required**, not optional. See [Convention ŌåÆ docs map](#convention--docs-map) below and [`.cursor/rules/docusaurus-docs.mdc`](./docusaurus-docs.mdc). Run `pnpm nx build DOCS` after doc edits.

### Convention ŌåÆ docs map

| Convention area | Update these docs (minimum) |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| FE (HTTP client, styling, store, routing, ŌĆ”) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/FE/` |
| BE (modules, filters, validation, routes, ŌĆ”) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/be/` |
| Mongoose / DB | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/mongodb.md` |
| Shared libs (`libs/dtos`, `libs/qu-constants`, `BE_ROUTES`, ŌĆ”) | Relevant `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/*.md` **and** setup page if cross-cutting (e.g. `06-nestjs-zod.md`) |
| Setup / tooling / git / Husky / env | Matching `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/NN-*.md` |
| AI policy / agent workflow | `apps/DOCS/docs/ai/policy.md` + root `AI.md` when judgement calls matter |

**Do not** land convention-only rule changes without the matching doc page(s). If a convention spans FE + BE (e.g. `BE_ROUTES`), update **both** app docs.

## Shared DTOs (`libs/dtos/src/lib/<domain>/`)

Organize by **domain folder** (e.g. `user/`, not flat files at `lib/` root unless legacy).

| Suffix | Purpose | Example |
| ------ | ------- | ------- |
| **`.model.ts`** | Zod mirror of a **persisted** Mongoose model (stored shape only; no plaintext passwords) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/user.model.ts` |
| **`.dto.ts`** | Flow/API schemas (signup, login, responses, ŌĆ”) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/signup.dto.ts` |

- **Model DTO** (`.model.ts`) reflects what is stored in the database ŌĆö not plaintext passwords or other transient input shapes.
- **Other DTOs** (`.dto.ts`) hold API/input validation (e.g. signup with plaintext password rules).
- Reuse shared Zod building blocks inside a domain (e.g. `password.schema.ts`) when multiple DTOs need the same rules ŌĆö **do not invent new suffixes** (e.g. no `.fields.ts`; Developer reverted `user.fields.ts` from a `/simplify` pass).
- Some duplication between `.model.ts` and `.dto.ts` is acceptable; do not extract field schemas into unofficial file types.
- NestJS wraps shared schemas with `createZodDto` in `apps/BE` ŌĆö keep wrappers in sync when adding schemas (see `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/06-nestjs-zod.md`).

## Mongoose (`mongoose/models/<domain>/`)

Per domain, always three files:

| File | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| **`*.schema.ts`** | Mongoose schema + `model()` registration |
| **`*.model.ts`** | Repository interfaces (`IUser`, `IUserDocument`, ŌĆ”) |
| **`*.paths.ts`** | Field path constants for queries, projections, and schema keys |

### Why `*.paths.ts`?

**Never hard-code field strings** in queries ŌĆö import from `*.paths.ts` so renames touch one file.

Example:

```ts
import { UserPaths } from '@quack/mongoose/models/user';

UserModel.findOne({ [UserPaths.email]: email });
```

### Mongoose directory (root)

```
mongoose/
Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ client.ts          # DB connection (ENV_KEYS, E2E URI switch)
Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ models/            # domain folders (user/, ŌĆ”)
Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ fixtures/          # test/dev fixture data
ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ tsconfig.json
```

## FE styling (Tailwind v4)

- **Nx scaffold** shipped Tailwind **v3** (`tailwind.config.js` + PostCSS); FE is migrated to **v4** (`tailwindcss@4`, `@tailwindcss/vite`).
- **Vite plugin** ŌĆö `@tailwindcss/vite` in `apps/FE/vite.config.mts` (not PostCSS `tailwindcss` plugin).
- **CSS-first theme** ŌĆö `apps/FE/src/styles.css`: `@import "tailwindcss"`, `@import "tw-animate-css"`, `@theme inline` for shadcn tokens; no `apps/FE/tailwind.config.js`.
- **shadcn CLI** ŌĆö `apps/FE/components.json` with `"config": ""`; add components via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add ŌĆ”` from `apps/FE`.

## FE dev tooling (development only)

- **[React Scan](https://react-scan.com/)** and **[React Grab](https://www.react-grab.com/)** ŌĆö `dev-entry.ts` ŌåÆ `dev-tools.ts` (dev only) ŌåÆ `main.tsx`. Scan uses a static import in `dev-tools.ts` (must run before React); Grab uses dynamic `import()` there. Production entry skips `dev-tools` entirely.
- **React Scan** ŌĆö visual re-render highlights for performance debugging.
- **React Grab** ŌĆö ŌīśC / Ctrl+C on a hovered element copies component context for coding agents.
- Docs: `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/FE/08-dev-tooling.md` ŌĆö **Dev-only tooling**.

## FE HTTP client (`apps/FE/src/api/`)

- **One shared axios instance** ŌĆö `axiosConfig.ts` exports the default client; **do not** call `axios.create()` elsewhere in FE.
- **`baseURL`** ŌĆö from `VITE_API_URL` via `ENV_KEYS` (see `.env.example`); never hard-code API hosts in FE.
- **Import** ŌĆö `import api from '@/api/axiosConfig'` (or relative `../axiosConfig` under `api/services/`).
- **`handleError.ts`** ŌĆö normalizes `unknown` / `AxiosError` into `ErrorResponse` from `@shared/dtos`; axios-specific codes/messages live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants/axios.constants.ts` (`AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`).
- **`services/`** ŌĆö domain axios call sites (e.g. `authService.ts`); import `BE_ROUTES` from `@shared/constants` for path segments ŌĆö **no magic route strings** in FE services.
- Interceptors (auth token, global errors) stay in `axiosConfig.ts` only.
- **`services/index.ts`** ŌĆö barrel re-export for domain services (e.g. `import { AuthService } from '@/api/services'`).

## FE Redux store (`apps/FE/src/store/`)

| Path | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| `slices/*.ts` | Redux Toolkit slices; each slice calls API services from `@/api/services/` in `createAsyncThunk` |
| `root-reducer.ts` | `combineReducers` ŌĆö register slices here |
| `store.ts` / `hooks.ts` | Store setup + typed `useAppDispatch` / `useAppSelector` |

### Slice thunks

- Import services from `@/api/services` (not axios directly in slices).
- Catch errors with `handleError` from `@/api/handleError` and `rejectWithValue` with `ErrorResponse` (`@shared/dtos`).
- Use **granular loading flags** per operation (`isSigningUp`, `isCreating`, ŌĆ”) ŌĆö avoid a single ambiguous `isLoading` when multiple ops can run.

### Slice hooks (`apps/FE/src/hooks/slices/`)

- One hook per slice (e.g. `useAuth.ts`) ŌĆö **unified interface** exposing slice state, selectors, and dispatch wrappers.
- **Developer rationale:** when slice shape changes, update a few slice-hook files instead of many consumers across pages and components.
- Slice hooks are for **action ops** (`create` / `update` / `delete` / `select` / `clear`) from component logic hooks ŌĆö **not** for `fetch*` orchestration.

## FE layered data flow

```
API service ŌåÆ Redux slice ŌåÆ Slice hook ŌåÆ Page Context ŌåÆ component logic hook ŌåÆ UI component
```

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
| ----- | -------- | -------------- |
| **API service** | `api/services/` | HTTP via shared `axiosConfig`; paths from `BE_ROUTES` |
| **Redux slice** | `store/slices/` | Async thunks, normalized state, granular loading/error flags |
| **Slice hook** | `hooks/slices/` | Typed facade over slice state + actions for consumers |
| **Page context** | `pages/<Page>/` or `contexts/` | **`fetch*` orchestration only** ŌĆö `useEffect` / `useEffectEvent` to load data; exposes shared `data`, `isLoading`, `error`, pagination; may use `useError` / `useSuccess` for toasts |
| **Component logic** | `useComponentName.ts` next to `ComponentName.tsx` | Local state, handlers, effects that are **not** fetch orchestration; calls slice-hook action ops |
| **UI component** | `ComponentName.tsx` | Presentational markup; minimal logic |

### Rules

- **Page context:** `fetch*` effects live here only; use `useEffectEvent` for effect callbacks ŌĆö do not put those callbacks in dependency arrays.
- **Component logic:** no `fetch*` effects ŌĆö delegate loads to page context; use slice hooks for mutations/select/clear.
- **Forms:** react-hook-form + `zodResolver` + shared DTOs from `@shared/dtos`; `useForm<z.input<typeof Schema>, unknown, z.output<typeof Schema>>` when defaults/transforms differ; child form components match parent input type.
- **Cleanup:** clear page-owned Redux state on unmount unless persistence is required (`redux-persist` blacklist when appropriate).

## FE pages (`apps/FE/src/pages/<Page>/`)

- One folder per page (e.g. `pages/auth/Login/`, `pages/auth/Signup/`): `Page.tsx` (UI) + `usePage.ts` (component logic hook).
- **Routing** uses `react-router` (`react-router-dom`): `<BrowserRouter>` in `main.tsx`, `<Routes>` + global `<Toaster/>` in `app/app.tsx`. Path segments live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants/routes.constants.ts` (`FE_ROUTES`, `FE_DEFAULT_ROUTE`) ŌĆö use them in `<Route>`, `<Navigate>`, and `<Link>`; no magic path strings in components.
- **Shared layout** ŌĆö colocate a layout next to the pages it serves (e.g. `pages/auth/AuthLayout.tsx`) and pass the form via `children`; do not duplicate the scene per page.
- Mutations (e.g. signup) use a component logic hook calling a slice hook ŌĆö **no page-context `fetch*` layer** when there is no data to load.

## FE system hooks (`apps/FE/src/hooks/`) vs slice hooks (`hooks/slices/`)

- **System hooks** live directly under `apps/FE/src/hooks/` ŌĆö cross-cutting, non-slice utilities: `use-toast.ts`, `use-error.ts`, `use-success.ts`.
- **Slice hooks** live under `apps/FE/src/hooks/slices/` ŌĆö one per Redux slice (`useAuth.ts`), the typed facade over slice state + actions.
- Do **not** put slice facades under `hooks/` root, and do **not** put generic utilities under `hooks/slices/`.

## FE constants (`apps/FE/src/utils/constants/`)

- `utils/constants/` is a **directory**, not a flat `constants.ts` file:
  - `index.ts` ŌĆö barrel (keeps `@/utils/constants` imports working).
  - `axios.constants.ts` ŌĆö `AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`.
  - `routes.constants.ts` ŌĆö `FE_ROUTES` (`HOME`, `LOGIN`, `SIGNUP`), `FE_DEFAULT_ROUTE`.
  - `toast-variants.constants.ts` ŌĆö `TOAST_VARIANTS = { SUCCESS, WARNING, ERROR }`.
- Add new constant groups as `*.constants.ts` files re-exported from the barrel ŌĆö do not reintroduce a single flat file.

## FE toast variants

- Classic **shadcn toast** (Radix `@radix-ui/react-toast`), **not** `sonner` ŌĆö typed `cva` `toastVariants` + reducer queue that `use-error` / `use-success` can drive.
- Variants: `default`, `success` (green), `warning` (amber), `error` (red / destructive); names centralized in `TOAST_VARIANTS`.
- `use-error` skips the generic network fallback message, fires the `error` variant for real API errors, then clears the slice error; `use-success` is the analogous success-message hook.
- Mount `<Toaster/>` once (in `app/app.tsx`).

## FE public assets (`apps/FE/public/`)

- Static assets (sprite sheets, etc.) live under `apps/FE/public/` and are served at the site root by Vite (e.g. `public/sprites/duckling.png` ŌåÆ `/sprites/duckling.png`).
- Sprite/duck visuals: `public/sprites/` holds the walking-duck sheets (`duckling.png`, `mallard.png`); canvas components live in `components/duck/`.

## Backend routes (`libs/qu-constants/src/lib/be-routes.constants.ts`)

| Artifact | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| **`BE_ROUTES` enum** | API path segments shared via `@shared/constants` |

- Define **every** BE endpoint path segment in `be-routes.constants.ts` ŌĆö global prefix (`BASE`), controller segments (`USERS`, ŌĆ”), and action segments (`SIGNUP`, ŌĆ”).
- **No magic route strings** in controllers or `main.ts` ŌĆö use `BE_ROUTES` in `@Controller`, `@Get`/`@Post`/ŌĆ”, and `setGlobalPrefix`.
- Place in `qu-constants` so the FE can import the same segments for API clients later.

## Backend feature modules (`apps/BE/src/<feature>/`)

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| **`<feature>.controller.ts`** | HTTP routes for the feature | `users/users.controller.ts` |
| **`<feature>.dto.ts`** | `createZodDto` wrappers for that featureŌĆÖs Zod schemas | `users/users.dto.ts` ŌåÆ `SignupDto` |
| **`<feature>.module.ts`** | Nest module wiring | `users/users.module.ts` |

- Colocate **DTO wrappers next to the controller** (`users/users.dto.ts`), not only in `app/app.dto.ts`.
- Shared Zod schemas stay in `libs/dtos`; BE wrappers import from `@shared/dtos`.

## Backend utilities (`apps/BE/src/utils/`)

| Location | Purpose | Example |
| -------- | ------- | ------- |
| **`*.util.ts`** | BE helpers (hashing, error parsing, ŌĆ”) | `password.util.ts`, `mongoose-error.handler.util.ts` |
| **`libs/<service>/`** | Wrappers for **external services** (S3, logger, email, ŌĆ”) | `utils/libs/s3/` |

- Do not use bare `utils/foo.ts` ŌĆö use the **`.util.ts`** suffix.
- External SDK clients belong under `utils/libs/<domain-name-for-service>/`, not at `utils/` root.

## Imports

- `@shared/dtos`, `@shared/constants` from apps and `mongoose/`
- **`@quack/mongoose/*`** ŌĆö repo Mongoose layer (`mongoose/` at repo root). **Do not** use deep relative imports (e.g. `../../../../mongoose/...`) or bare `mongoose/...` paths that collide with the npm `mongoose` package.
- App-local: `@/*` under `apps/FE` or `apps/BE`
- App tsconfigs: `baseUrl: "../.."` and extend `./tsconfig.json` (FE must keep `jsx`)

